    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Investigate and Modify\r\n\r\n### **Extracting Individual Digits**\r\nIn many programs, we need to **break down a number into its individual digits**, such as when displaying digits separately or performing calculations on each digit.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:** Copy and paste the following code into your program, then run it.  \r\nObserve how it extracts digits from `num` one by one.\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nint num = 12345;\r\n\r\nSystem.out.println(\"Original number: \" + num);\r\n\r\nwhile (num > 0) {\r\n    int lastDigit = num % 10;  \r\n    System.out.println(\"Extracted Digit: \" + lastDigit);\r\n    num /= 10;  // Remove the last digit\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nHow does the `%` operator help extract digits?\r\n",
    "mini_rubric": "false",
    "submittable": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "false",
    "csa_view_mode": "console",
